<h2 id="bookQuote">"Fools have a habit of believing that everything written by a famous author is admirable.<br>For my part, I read only
to please myself and like only what suits my taste." - Voltaire</h2>
<p class="intro">Much like Voltaire, I have a particular taste in literature. I do not have a great love for non-fiction books, nor
am I too jazzed about real-world fiction. If I'm reading, it's usually because I want to escape the mundanity of life.
For me, fantasy and science fiction are the genres of choice. I love imagining new worlds and types of people and I find
that these oft-maligned genres explore the same themes and issues that "more respectable" books do, often to a greater degree.</p>
