                <h2>Dune</h2>
                <p class="author">Frank Herbert</p>
                <p><i>Dune</i> is a book that I really wish more people would read. So many pass it by because it holds
                 the label of "Science Fiction." It is so much more than that. A sprawling epic, larger even than Tolkien's
                masterpiece, <i>Dune</i> explores the political intrigue, drama, and betrayal surrounding the galaxy's most
                important planet and its most valuable resource. With prose that makes one feel as if one is actually on
                a desert planet, Frank Herbert immerses the reader in his universe. Truly a masterpiece.</p>
